On the anniversary of the September 11th attacks, Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the Flight 93 National Memorial in Shanksville, Pennsylvania. He paid tribute to the 40 heroes of Flight 93 and all those who lost their lives on that day. Pence also extended condolences to the families affected by Hurricane Irma and pledged support for recovery efforts. He spoke about his personal experience on 9/11 and how the heroes of Flight 93 saved many lives, including his own. Pence emphasized the ongoing threat of terrorism and the need to fight against it. He also highlighted the commitment of the United States to eliminate terrorist organizations and protect its citizens. Pence expressed gratitude on behalf of the nation and his own family to the heroes of Flight 93, stating that their memory will always be honored and cherished.